On August 16, 2022, the President signed into law H.R. 5376, which focuses on reconciling the Federal Budget in accordance with the Fiscal Year 2022 Budget Resolution. The law addresses various issues including climate change, health care, taxation, and the Federal deficit. It achieves these goals through direct appropriations, the creation of new programs, modifications to existing programs, and changes to the tax code. The President expressed gratitude to several individuals, including Leader Schumer, Speaker Pelosi, Senators Manchin, Carper, Wyden, Sinema, Durbin, Murray, Stabenow, Klobuchar, Warner, and Sanders, as well as Leader Hoyer, Whip Clyburn, and Representatives Neal, Pallone, Yarmuth, and Castor, along with other Senate and House Democrats.